thread.title: Duxbury locks it up
thread.title_full: Duxbury locks it up | Boston Herald

author: Herald Staff
title: Duxbury locks it up
text:
Bobby Maimaron completed 14-of-20 passes for 133 yards and five touchdowns as No. 6 Duxbury (5-1) defeated Silver Lake , 42-3, to clinch the Patriot Keenan title yesterday.
Junior Kevin O’Brien caught two touchdowns and added an interception as Braintree (3-3) blanked Brookline , 41-0, in a Bay State Carey matchup.
Randy Alay’s third field goal of the game, a 28-yarder as time ran out, gave Waltham (2-4) a 16-14 win over Lincoln-Sudbury in the Dual County Large.
Mekhai Johnson ran for 291 yards and four touchdowns, giving him 11 on the season, as Belmont (2-4) defeated Winchester , 35-28, in the Middlesex Liberty.
Zach Lanzetta and Blake Hill each rushed for a touchdown as Milford (3-3) defeated Sharon , 17-7, in a Hockomock Davenport matchup.
Marcus McBean had 17 carries for 250 yards and three touchdowns as Archbishop Williams (4-2) defeated Austin Prep , 35-0, in a Catholic Central Large contest.
Ivan Mertilus’ 1-yard TD run in the second quarter was all the scoring as St. Clement (4-2) remained atop the Catholic Central Small with an 8-0 win over Marian/Keefe Tech .
Mike Trifone and Scott Peary combined to rush for 235 yards and two TDs as Northeast (2-4) defeated Whittier , 20-14, in the Commonwealth Athletic Large.
Cameron Reis carried 22 times for 214 yards and a touchdown, while the Bishop Connolly (6-0) defense extended its scoreless streak to 14 quarters in a 27-0 win over Diman in the Mayflower Large.
Agyei Alfred rushed for a pair of touchdowns and Shawn Kelly added 136 yards on the ground as Minuteman (1-5) snapped a 12-game losing streak by edging Chelsea , 16-14, in a Commonwealth Athletic Small contest.
Alex Small ran for 150 yards and a touchdown, while also recovering a fumble as Nantucket (6-0) defeated West Bridgewater , 14-6, to clinch the Mayflower Small title.
Omari Davis ran for three scores as St. George’s (4-0) defeated Thayer Academy , 49-21, in the Independent School League Small. . . . Jalen Martinez ran for 139 yards and four scores as Brooks (2-2) rolled to a 49-6 win over St. Mark’s .
Shane Smith recorded 15 tackles and Cam Macri scored three touchdowns as Governor’s Academy (4-0) defeated St. Paul’s , 39-13, in an Independent School League crossover contest.
Tristan Moulton rushed for four TDs as Proctor (3-1) defeats Holderness , 57-34, in the Evergreen League.
James Huff’s 22-yard interception return for a score got South Shore (4-2) off and running to a 30-6 nonleague victory over Cape Cod Tech , handing coach Derek Mariani his 100th victory in his 17 years at the helm.
Boys soccer
Sophomore David Laine scored a hat trick in the final 14 minutes to propel Bourne (5-4-3) over South Coast Conference foe Fairhaven , 3-2.
It was a day of firsts for BC High (8-4-1), as senior Joe Cipullo and sophmores Ryan Cuozzo and Durmuid McGonagle all scored their first varsity goals in a 7-2 victory over Malden Catholic in Catholic Conference play.
Girls soccer
In a Bay State Conference crossover game, Natick (9-1-3) beat Braintree , 3-0, with two goals from sophomore Rachel Jasinski.
Dan Ventura, Kevin Barrucci, Marcelo Rossetti and Brian Roach compiled this report.
